      name: 'Why take vitamin D and zinc together?',
      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Vitamin D and zinc are the two most common nutrient deficiencies linked to impaired immune function. Vitamin D activates T-cells (adaptive immune response) and modulates inflammatory cytokines, while zinc is required for the development and function of neutrophils, natural killer cells, and macrophages (innate immune response). Together, they support both arms of the immune system through complementary mechanisms. A 2020 meta-analysis found that individuals deficient in both vitamin D and zinc had significantly higher rates of respiratory infections. Correcting both deficiencies simultaneously provides more comprehensive immune support than supplementing either nutrient alone.' },
