    <h2 id="why-d-zinc">Why Vitamin D and Zinc Are the Ultimate Immune Combination</h2>

    <p>Vitamin D and zinc support immune function through complementary but distinct mechanisms. Vitamin D activates T-cells — the adaptive immune cells that recognize and remember specific pathogens. Without adequate vitamin D, T-cells remain in a dormant state and cannot mount an effective targeted response to infections. Zinc, meanwhile, is required for the development and function of innate immune cells — neutrophils, natural killer cells, and macrophages — that provide the first line of defense against all pathogens. Together, they ensure both arms of your immune system are fully operational.</p>

